line_1: That scatter'd fever, agony, and death!
line_2: Sick Nature sunk before the mortal breath,

line_1: What funerals has thy cruel ravage spread!
line_2: What eyes have flow'd! what noble bosoms bled!

line_1: What eyes have flow'd! what noble bosoms bled!
line_2: What funerals has thy cruel ravage spread!

line_1: Here let Reflection fix her sober view:
line_2: O think, who suffer, and who sigh with you.

line_1: O think, who suffer, and who sigh with you.
line_2: Here let Reflection fix her sober view:

line_1: See, rudely snatch'd, in all her pride of charms,
line_2: Bright Granby from a youthful husband's arms!

line_1: Bright Granby from a youthful husband's arms!
line_2: See, rudely snatch'd, in all her pride of charms,

line_1: In climes far distant, see that husband mourn;
line_2: His arms revers'd, his recent laurel torn!

line_1: His arms revers'd, his recent laurel torn!
line_2: In climes far distant, see that husband mourn;

line_1: Behold again, at Fate's imperious call,
line_2: In one dread instant blooming Lincoln fall!

line_1: In one dread instant blooming Lincoln fall!
line_2: Behold again, at Fate's imperious call,

line_1: See her lov'd Lord with speechless anguish bend!
line_2: And, mixing tears with his, thy noblest friend,

line_1: And, mixing tears with his, thy noblest friend,
line_2: See her lov'd Lord with speechless anguish bend!

line_1: Thy Pelham turn on heaven his streaming eye:
line_2: Again in Her, he sees a Brother die.

line_1: Again in Her, he sees a Brother die.
line_2: Thy Pelham turn on heaven his streaming eye:

line_1: And He, who long, unshaken and serene,
line_2: Had Death, in each dire form of terror, seen,

line_1: Had Death, in each dire form of terror, seen,
line_2: And He, who long, unshaken and serene,

line_1: Thro' worlds unknown, o'er unknown oceans tost,
line_2: By Love subdu'd, now weeps a Consort lost:

line_1: By Love subdu'd, now weeps a Consort lost:
line_2: Thro' worlds unknown, o'er unknown oceans tost,

line_1: Now, sunk to fondness, all the man appears,
line_2: His front dejected, and his soul in tears!

line_1: His front dejected, and his soul in tears!
line_2: Now, sunk to fondness, all the man appears,

line_1: Yet more: nor thou the muse's voice disdain,
line_2: Who fondly tries to soothe a Father's pain —

line_1: Who fondly tries to soothe a Father's pain —
line_2: Yet more: nor thou the muse's voice disdain,

line_1: Let thy calm eye survey the suffering ball:
line_2: See kingdoms round thee verging to their fall!

line_1: See kingdoms round thee verging to their fall!
line_2: Let thy calm eye survey the suffering ball:

line_1: What spring had promis'd, and what autumn yields,
line_2: The bread of thousands ravish'd from their fields!

line_1: The bread of thousands ravish'd from their fields!
line_2: What spring had promis'd, and what autumn yields,

line_1: See youth and age, th'ignoble and the great,
line_2: Swept to one grave, in one promiscuous fate!

line_1: Swept to one grave, in one promiscuous fate!
line_2: See youth and age, th'ignoble and the great,

line_1: Hear Europe groan! hear all her nations mourn!
line_2: And be a private wound with patience borne.

line_1: And be a private wound with patience borne.
line_2: Hear Europe groan! hear all her nations mourn!

line_1: Think too: and Reason will confirm the thought:
line_2: Thy cares, for Her, are to their period brought.

line_1: Thy cares, for Her, are to their period brought.
line_2: Think too: and Reason will confirm the thought:

line_1: Yes, She, fair pattern to a failing age,
line_2: With wit, chastis'd, with sprightly temper, sage;

line_1: With wit, chastis'd, with sprightly temper, sage;
line_2: Yes, She, fair pattern to a failing age,

line_1: Whom each endearing name could recommend,
line_2: Whom all became, wife, sister, daughter, friend,

line_1: Whom all became, wife, sister, daughter, friend,
line_2: Whom each endearing name could recommend,

line_1: Unwarp'd by folly, and by vice unstain'd,
line_2: The prize of virtue has, for ever gain'd!

line_1: The prize of virtue has, for ever gain'd!
line_2: Unwarp'd by folly, and by vice unstain'd,

line_1: From life escap'd, and safe on that calm shore
line_2: Where sin, and pain, and error are no more,

line_1: Where sin, and pain, and error are no more,
line_2: From life escap'd, and safe on that calm shore

line_1: She now no change, nor you a fear can feel:
line_2: Death, to her fame, has fix'd th' eternal seal!

line_1: Death, to her fame, has fix'd th' eternal seal!
line_2: She now no change, nor you a fear can feel:
